text2:
As we age through life's stages, our understanding of time and mortality evolves:

• As children, we live in the present and time seems endless. Mortality is not grasped. 

• As young adults, we live for the future and feel immortal. Time is abundant.

• In middle age, as responsibilities mount and health declines, time feels fleeting. Mortality looms larger.

• In old age, the past is more present, the future foreshortened, and mortality most keenly felt. Time is precious.
